  "content": "\u003cp\u003eI may have a controversial opinion about LinkedIn.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI have a personal policy of only accepting LinkedIn connection requests of people I have already met, talked to, worked with, or interacted with in some way. I may also accept a connection request if someone attaches a message that shows real engagement or interest. If you comment on my posts I\u0026#39;m also way more likely to accept! But if you have typed zero words towards me I\u0026#39;m really not sure what you\u0026#39;re getting from a connection with me and vica versa.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhy do I do this? I figure that my network should reflect those who I can reasonable vouch for. If enough people do this then the linkedin network would reflect a kind of network of social trust. Shallow \u0026quot;connection farming\u0026quot; is strange to me.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAm I doing LinkedIn wrong? Should I want as many connections as possible?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI posted this on LinkedIn as well. Any comments?\u003cbr /\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/sudorandom_i-may-have-a-controversial-opinion-about-activity-7165349218042245121-3TIS\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ehttps://www.\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"ellipsis\"\u003elinkedin.com/posts/sudorandom_\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"invisible\"\u003ei-may-have-a-controversial-opinion-about-activity-7165349218042245121-3TIS\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
